n\nclass Solution:\n    def maximumTripletValue(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        n = len(nums)\n        right = [nums[-1]] * n\n        for i in range(n - 2, -1, -1):\n            right[i] = max(nums[i], right[i + 1])\n        sl = SortedList([nums[0]])\n        ans = 0\n        for j in range(1, n - 1):\n            if right[j + 1] > nums[j]:\n                i = sl.bisect_left(nums[j]) - 1\n                if i >= 0:\n                    ans = max(ans, sl[i] - nums[j] + right[j + 1])\n            sl.add(nums[j])\n        return ans\n```\n\nThis solution uses a `SortedList` to keep track of the smallest elements seen so far, and a `right` array to keep track of the maximum elements to the right of each index. It iterates through the list, updating the `SortedList` and checking for valid triplets to compute the maximum value.", "estimated_date": 1709424000000}